CLOSE Anna Mae Blessing, of Fountain Hills, is accused of fatally shooting her 72-year-old son because he planned to put her in an assisted-living facility.
Arizona RepublicAnna Mae Blessing (Photo: Maricopa County Sheriff's Office)Charges against a 92-year-old woman accused of fatally shooting her son may be dropped, as she is in hospice care after suffering a stroke in jail.
Anna Mae Blessing, who is charged with first-degree murder and aggravated assault with a deadly weapon, was absent from her scheduled hearing Monday in Maricopa County Superior Court.
Blessing is accused of shooting her son July 2 because he wanted to move her into an assisted living facility.
She shared a Fountain Hills apartment with her son and his girlfriend, but Blessing and other family members told deputies the relationship became strained.